text:
Atleticano falou demais antes do jogo. "Massacrar", "demolir", "destruir"... e tudo o que vimos foi o bagunçado Flamengo vencer o "todo poderoso" Galo.

Galo de verdade é o Arthur Antunes Coimbra. O Atlético é o Botafogo de Minas. Bastou perder pra começar o chororô. Mó vergonha, pô. Um timaço ficar com esse papinho. Fizeram pouco do Flamengo e perderam. Acontece.

Agora, o que seria do Flamengo sem a individualidade dos seus jogadores? Se faltou esquema tático, sobrou coração lá atrás e técnica lá na frente. O Michael está carregando o time lá no ataque.

Agora, o Leo Pereira foi o destaque. E o que seria do Flamengo sem a saída de bola do William Arão? O verdadeiro craque do time.

text:
Ezekiel 12

 1. Yet the word of the Lord came to me, saying:
 2. Son of man, you dwell in the midst of the rebellious house, which has eyes to see and does not see, and has ears to hear and does not hear;  because it's a rebel house.
 3. Thou therefore, son of man, prepare thyself the things to move into exile, and change by day in their sight;  and from thy place thou shalt move to another place in their sight;  it may well be that they notice it, even though they are house rebels.
 4. In their sight, therefore, shalt thou take out thy things by day, as for moving;  then thou shalt go out in the afternoon in their sight, as one who goes into exile.
 5. Make for yourself, in their sight, an opening in the wall, and that way you will come out.
 6. In their sight you shall carry your things on your shoulders, and in the dark you shall carry them, and you shall cover your face, so that you do not see the ground;  because I have made you a sign to the house of Israel.
 7. And I did so, as I was commanded: I took out my junk during the day, as for exile;  then in the afternoon I made an opening in the wall with my hand;  in the dark I came out, carrying them on my shoulders, within sight of them.
 8. And the word of the Lord came to me in the morning, saying,
 9. Son of man, did not the house of Israel ask thee, that rebellious house, What are you doing?
 10. Say to them, Thus saith the Lord God: This oracle refers to the prince in Jerusalem, and to all the house of Israel that are in the midst of it.
 11. Say: I am your sign: As I have done, so shall it be done to them;  will go into exile into captivity,
 12. And the prince that is in the midst of them will carry the junk on his shoulders, and come out in the dark;  he will make an opening in the wall and come out through it;  he will cover your face, for with his eyes you will not see the ground.
 13. I will also spread my net over him, and he shall be caught in my snare;  and I will take him to Babylon, to the land of the Chaldeans;  yet he will not see her, though he will die there.
 14. And all that are round about him for his help, and all his troops, I will scatter to every wind;  and I will unsheathe the sword behind them.
 15. So they will know that I am the Lord, when I scatter them among the nations and scatter them among the countries.
 16. But I will leave a few of them, escapes from the sword, from famine, and from pestilence, that they may confess all their abominations among the nations whither they go;  and they will know that I am the Lord.
 17. Yet the word of the Lord came to me, saying:
 18. Son of man, eat your bread with trembling, and drink your water with trembling and with fear.
 19. And thou shalt say unto the people of the land, Thus saith the Lord God concerning the inhabitants of Jerusalem, in the land of Israel: Their bread they shall eat with fear, and their water they shall drink with fear, for their land shall be deprived of its abundance for cause of the violence of all who inhabit it.
 20. And the inhabited cities will be laid waste, and the land will be desolate;  and ye shall know that I am the Lord.
 21. And the word of the Lord came to me again, saying,
 22. Son of man, what is this proverb you have in the land of Israel, saying, The days are wide open, and all vision fails?
 23. Therefore say to them, Thus saith the Lord God: I will make this proverb to cease, and it shall no more be used in Israel;  but tell them, The days are at hand, and the fulfillment of every vision.
 24. For there shall be no more vain visions, nor flattering divinations, in the midst of the house of Israel.
 25. For I am the Lord;  I will speak, and the word I speak will be fulfilled.  It will no longer be delayed;  for in our days, O rebellious house, I will speak the word and do it, saith the Lord God.
 26. The word of the Lord came to me, saying:
 27. Son of man, behold, they of the house of Israel say: The vision which this one sees is for many days to come, and he prophesies of times that are far off.
 28. Therefore say to them, Thus saith the Lord GOD; None of my words shall be delayed any longer, but the word which I have spoken shall be fulfilled, saith the Lord GOD.

É difícil entender esses comentaristas , críticos e até a torcida que tripudiam o Renato.

Todos sabem que a defesa do Mengo é fraca, o Renato está tirando leite de pedra, não tem reposição de jogadores , o Diego está lento e amarra o time do Flamengo. Fazer o que ???
Mesmo assim o Renato bateu o grande Atlético do raivoso Cuca que não sabe perder.
A derrota para o Atlético Paranaense foi mais por azar e a escalação do Diego porque é um time muito fraco e teve muita sorte deu tudo certo, teve até falha do goleiro.
Creio que o Renato é milagreiro, sem Arrascaeta, sem Davi Luiz e tantos outros continua no páreo.

text:
Léo Pereira joga num time que gastou demais pra montar o elenco que tem, e já é um jogador contestadíssimo por não estar muito à altura dos zagueiros que seriam os titulares (R. Caio e David Luiz). E se você não é flamenguista, não deve saber que o L. Pereira recebe críticas já há um bom tempo.

Então tem que ser criticado. E se jogar bem (não estou falando de ganhar, mas sim de jogar bem), ele terá o respeito da torcida.

A torcida do Palmeiras fez o mesmo com o Felipe Melo. Ele é criticado pra caramba, mas cancelou completamente o Hulk na Libertadores e ajudou o time a conquistar a vaga pra final. Com isso, foi exaltado pela torcida. Por que você não chama a torcida do Palmeiras de modinha por isso também?
